Get transaction details or execute serialized transactions

Usage: soma tx [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  info                     Get transaction details by digest
  execute-serialized       Execute from serialized transaction bytes
  execute-signed           Execute using pre-signed transaction bytes and signatures
  execute-combined-signed  Execute a combined sender-signed transaction
  help                     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --client.config <CONFIG>  Sets the file storing the state of our user accounts (an empty one will be created if missing)
      --client.env <ENV>        The SOMA environment to use. This must be present in the current config file
  -y, --yes                     Create a new soma config without prompting if none exists
      --json                    Output as JSON
  -h, --help                    Print help

EXAMPLES:
    soma tx DIGEST_BASE58
    soma tx execute-serialized <TX_BYTES>
    soma tx execute-signed --tx-bytes <BYTES> --signatures <SIGS>
